On 22-Sep-05, at 7:07 AM, mark greene wrote:

Hello Everyone,

I am new to the list and I would like some advice.Upon returning to  
the US I will buy a baywindow bus, my question is what is the best  
engine to use in the van or single cab.


Two questions:

1. Will the Jeep 2.5L fit under the engine top cover of a 68 - 79 vw  
van, or will I need to raise the access lid?

2. Is there a better engine to use that will fit my needs, while  
maintaining simplicity and reliability.

My thoughts are an engine conversion to a Jeep 2.5L . It will be used  
for hauling wood, plasterboard, stones, and other house renovation  
materials,  one part of the solution an engine with good low-end toque.

Being retired and single I also like to travel, another desire is an  
engine that will maintain around 25 mpg at 60 to 70 mph on the  
highway. Here again I think the Jeep engine will fit my needs.

The final part is long term reliability and simplicity,  I am willing  
to sacrifice some  fuel consumption for simplicity, but I want to  
maintain at least 20 mpg on the highway.
